# Review Skill

When invoked:

1. Get the full diff vs main:
   ```bash
   git log --oneline main...HEAD
   git diff main...HEAD
   ```
2. Read the actual changed files — don't review from diff alone for complex changes
3. Apply the **Reviewer agent** persona with full checklist:
   - Correctness (logic, edge cases, error paths)
   - Design (abstraction level, coupling, API clarity)
   - Tests (coverage, mock divergence, assert vs expect)
   - Security (injection, bounds, secrets)
   - Style (non-blocking)
4. Output the structured review report with APPROVE / NEEDS WORK / CRITICAL verdict

## Scope
- Review all commits on this branch since it diverged from `main`
- Not just the latest commit — all of them

## After Review
- If APPROVE: the user can merge
- If NEEDS WORK: list the specific files and lines to fix
- If CRITICAL: stop — don't approve until the critical issue is resolved
